Defendant Carol L Weggen in court with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called for sentencing hearing. Defendant's son presents statements to the court.  Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  
  -  2  YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2  YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  4 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  any victims or their residence/property
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
 
RESTITUTION:  $29,176.91 (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines); ($12,936.18 to American Family, $11,240.73 Crime victim fund, $5000.00 Progressive Insur.)

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

TRANSCRIPT FEE:  $32.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

REVOCATION OF DRIVER'S LICENSE:  24 MONTHS

CONDITION TIME: 9 MONTHS HUBER STAYED LAST 4 MONTHS to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours. Defendant to commencing this sentence by November 2, 2015 @ 6 pm. 

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

BAIL TO REMAIN ON THIS FILE UNTIL THE RESTITUTION HEARING
  Restitution hearing scheduled for December 10, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
